external_knowledge:
Top contributors refer to individuals who have made the most significant contributions to a particular field or community, in this case, programming languages; 
A programming language is a set of rules and instructions that a computer can understand and execute, such as Python, Java, and C++; 
Accessing a language refers to the act of viewing or interacting with the language's documentation, tutorials, or other resources; 
Contributing to a language involves creating new content, modifying existing content, or providing feedback to improve the language.
